    {
      "name": "Sichuan Bang Bang Chicken with Spicy Peanut Sauce",
      "instructions": [
        "Gently poach the chicken breasts in a pot of simmering water with a slice of ginger and a spring onion until fully cooked through (about 15 minutes).",
        "While the chicken is cooking, prepare the peanut sauce: in a bowl, whisk the peanut butter, soy sauce, Chinkiang vinegar, sugar, minced garlic, and chili oil together with a splash of hot water until smooth and creamy.",
        "Remove the chicken, let it cool slightly, then shred the meat into thin strips using your fingers or two forks.",
        "Finely slice the remaining spring onions.",
        "Plate the shredded chicken, drizzle the rich, spicy-sweet peanut sauce generously on top, and garnish with spring onions and toasted sesame seeds."
      ],
      "required_ingredients": [
        {
          "name": "Chicken breasts",
          "amount": "300g"
