      "name": "Sweet and Savory Peanut Kung Pao Chicken (Fusion Style)",
      "instructions": [
        "Dice the chicken breasts into bite-sized pieces and season with a pinch of salt.",
        "In a small bowl, whisk together the peanut butter, soy sauce, honey, rice vinegar, minced garlic, and minced ginger. Add 2 tablespoons of warm water to loosen the paste.",
        "Heat a splash of oil in a skillet over high heat. Add the chicken and sauté until golden brown and cooked through (about 6-8 minutes).",
        "Pour the sweet and savory peanut sauce directly into the skillet, stirring constantly to coat the chicken as the sauce bubbles and caramelizes.",
        "Toss in the sliced spring onions and dried chili flakes, stirring for an additional minute before serving hot over rice."
      ],
      "required_ingredients": [
