      "name": "Classic Cantonese Steamed Sea Bass",
      "instructions": [
        "Julienne the ginger and spring onions into very fine strips.",
        "Place the sea bass fillets on a heatproof plate, top with half of the ginger, and drizzle with Shaoxing wine.",
        "Steam the fish over high heat for 6-8 minutes until cooked through.",
        "Carefully discard the accumulated fish liquid and cooked ginger from the plate.",
        "Scatter the fresh spring onions and remaining ginger over the steamed fish.",
        "Heat vegetable oil in a small saucepan until smoking hot, then pour it over the ginger and spring onions to release their aroma.",
        "Mix light soy sauce, hot water, and sugar, then pour it around the plate (not directly on the fish) and garnish with fresh coriander."
